INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thb2300','letter','1781-02-12','Litchfield','CT','US','Theodosia','Prevost','','Aaron','Burr','','Your opinion of Voltaire pleases me, as it proves your judgment above being biased by the prejudices of others. The English, from national jealousy and enmity to the French, detract him.','ltr_thb2300.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thb2301','letter','1781-03-06','Litchfield','CT','US','Theodosia','Prevost','','Aaron','Burr','','How strangely we pass through life! All acknowledge themselves mortal and immortal; and yet prefer the trifles of to-day to the treasures of eternity.','ltr_thb2301.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thb2302','letter','1781-05-00','Litchfield','CT','US','Theodosia','Prevost','','Aaron','Burr','','Our being the subject of much inquiry, conjecture, and calumny, is no more than we ought to expect. My attention to you was ever pointed enough to attract the observation of those who visited the house.','ltr_thb2302.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thb2303','letter','1781-09-11','Sharon','CT','US','Theodosia','Prevost','','Aaron','Burr','','We were obliged to Dr. Cutting for the most pleasing account of your health and spirits. Also, of your great progress in law.','ltr_thb2303.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thb2304','letter','1783-03-25','Albany','NY','US','Theodosia','Prevost','','Aaron','Burr','','Some think absence tends to increase affection; the greater part that it wears it away. I believe neither, but that it only tends to prove how far the heart is capable of loving','ltr_thb2304.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thb2305','letter','1783-08-14','Albany','NY','US','Theodosia','Prevost','','Aaron','Burr','','When she sleeps, I watch anxiously; when she wakes, anxious fears accompany every motion. I talked of my love towards her, but I knew it not till put to this unhappy test.','ltr_thb2305.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thb2306','letter','1784-02-22','New York','NY','US','Theodosia','Prevost','','Aaron','Burr','','My Aaron had scarce quitted the door when I regretted my passiveness. Why did I consent to his departure? Can interest repay the sacrifice?','ltr_thb2306.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thb2308','letter','1785-04-00','New York','NY','US','Theodosia','Prevost','','Aaron','Burr','','I persuade myself this is the last day you spend in Philadelphia.','ltr_thb2308.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thb2309','letter','1785-05-00','New York','NY','US','Theodosia','Prevost','','Aaron','Burr','','Your dear little daughter seeks you twenty times a day; calls you to your meals, and will not suffer your chair to be filled by any of the family.','ltr_thb2309.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thb2310','letter','1785-05-00','New York','NY','US','Theodosia','Prevost','','Aaron','Burr','','I have a little fever hanging about me, which tends to depress my spirits for the time. ','ltr_thb2310.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thb2311','letter','1785-04-00','New York','NY','US','Theodosia','Prevost','','Aaron','Burr','','The family as you left it. Thy Theodosia\'s health and spirits increase daily. Bartow\'s industry and utility are striking to the family and strangers.','ltr_thb2311.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thb2312','letter','1785-05-22','New York','NY','US','Theodosia','Prevost','','Aaron','Burr','','Your dear little Theo. grows the most engaging child you ever saw. She frequently talks of, and calls on, her dear papa.','ltr_thb2312.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thb2313','letter','1785-08-28','New York','NY','US','Theodosia','Prevost','','Aaron','Burr','','I really believe, my dear, few parents can boast of children whose minds are so prone to virtue.','ltr_thb2313.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thb2314','letter','1785-08-29','New York','NY','US','Theodosia','Prevost','','Aaron','Burr','','Our little daughter\'s health has improved beyond my expectations.','ltr_thb2314.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thb2315','letter','1785-09-25','New York','NY','US','Theodosia','Prevost','','Aaron','Burr','','I was relieved, delighted, till the recollection of the storm you have since weathered took place.','ltr_thb2315.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thb2316','letter','1785-09-27','New York','NY','US','Theodosia','Prevost','','Aaron','Burr','','I have counted the hours till evening; since that, the minutes, and am still on the watch; the stage not arrived: it is a cruel delay. Your health, your tender frame, how are they supported!','ltr_thb2316.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thb2317','letter','1786-08-00','New York','NY','US','Theodosia','Prevost','','Aaron','Burr','','If you finish your causes before court is over, cannot you look at us, even should you return to the manor?','ltr_thb2317.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thb2318','letter','1787-11-00','New York','NY','US','Theodosia','Prevost','','Aaron','Burr','','What language can express the joy, the gratitude of Theodosia? Stage after stage without a line. Thy usual punctuality gave room for every fear; various conjectures filled every breast.','ltr_thb2318.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thb2319','letter','1787-11-00','New York','NY','US','Theodosia','Prevost','','Aaron','Burr','','My health is better. As I fondly believe this the most interesting intelligence I can give thee, I make it my preamble.','ltr_thb2319.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thb2320','letter','1791-06-30','New York','NY','US','Theodosia','Prevost','','Aaron','Burr','','The Edwardses dine with me; they had taken lodgings previous to their arrival, in consequence of a report made them by the little Bodowins ... that my house was too small and inconvenient to admit of a spare bed.','ltr_thb2320.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thb2321','letter','1791-07-23','Pelham','NY','US','Theodosia','Prevost','','Aaron','Burr','','I was apprehensive travelling in the heat and bad accommodations would check your recovery. Do return home as soon as possible; or, rather, come to Pelham','ltr_thb2321.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_thb2322','letter','1791-07-27','Pelham','NY','US','Theodosia','Prevost','','Aaron','Burr','','Poor Dr. Wright had his house two days ago burnt to the ground, and all the furniture, with every article of clothing both of themselves and the children.','ltr_thb2322.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Project Gutenberg\'s Memoirs of Aaron Burr, Volume 1., by Matthew L. Davis, 1836');
